-------MY SQL SERVER --------

DECLARE @count INT
SET @count=20;
WHILE (@count>0)
BEGIN SELECT REPLICATE('* ',@count)
    SET @count=@count-1;
END

/* here in SQL, we use DECLARE to declare a variable. we've to use '@' before the variable name. and we've to use the '@' in every part.

REPLICATE('string', integer) function is used to repeat a string for n(integer) amount.
SET is used to set the value of the variable. 

*/
